messages.message:
@Dominic Fannjiang I’m encountering this issue doing enterprise UATs, which I believe is related to the recent upgrades to `scikit-learn`. What are the steps for fixing this issue?
```Unexpected error registering your user defined functions in /Consumer Lending DL (UK)/modules/Proof of Address.refiner/scripts. Error: Error registering your UDF: No module named 'sklearn.tree.tree', line 49 of ib/market/ib_semantics/semantic_types/address.py```
cc @andy This is blocking my Flow Review uat. I’ll do other UATs in the meantime.
can you link me to the flow
Works now, thanks! Is this fix on a per flow basis or a platform level fix?
Dang. Do we have docs on how to fix our flow if we see this issue again?

but yea basically, old versions ib_semantics can no longer be used because the serialized model it uses can no longer be loaded. so the fix is just to not register it in the udf scripts that register it.

I just commented out everything in `https://uat.dogfood.instabase.com/kerry/demos/fs/Instabase%20Drive/Use%20Cases/Consumer%2[…]0DL%20(UK)/modules/Proof%20of%20Address.refiner/scripts/ (https://uat.dogfood.instabase.com/kerry/demos/fs/Instabase%20Drive/Use%20Cases/Consumer%20Lending%20DL%20(UK)/modules/Proof%20of%20Address.refiner/scripts/)import-ib_semantics (1).py
